Text.Value: *The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*

EditorData.SFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face
EditorData.VFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face

Text.Value: *Pacified, the guard allows you and Minthara to pass.*
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
*The guard isn't convinced - you'll have to fight your way out.*
What prisoner?
*The guard is happy to let you pass - Minthara is rather less happy about your choice of words.*
*The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
She's with me - stand down.
*You avoided a fight this time, but bullying your way out of Moonrise is a risky proposition.*
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Delete if you are talking to a companion.
EditorData.SFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face
EditorData.VFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face

Text.Value: *As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*

EditorData.SFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face
EditorData.VFXTags: mark of the absolute on the guard face

Text.Value: *A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
*Minthara is supposed to be in a cell - you have some explaining to do.*
I think she serves rather well as my personal servant, don't you?
Attack.
Minthara's been released - and that frees up a cell for people like you, who challenge their betters.
Just look at her. You've nothing to fear from this drooling idiot.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
*Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
*You have no authority here - the guards serve a more powerful master.*

Synopsis: This dialogues occurs when you are seen close to Minthara once she is freed from Moonrise Towers. It needs to be a GEB dialogue, and thus unvoiced - so Minthara won't speak. Instead, she'll react to the outcome with an AD once the guard has left / died.
